00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:10.010
JAMES GRIME: You'll find 42
comes up a lot in comedy and

00:04:10.010 --> 00:04:13.795
other shows, partly because of
Douglas Adams and because he

00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:17.690
used it, but partly because
it's just a funny sound.

00:04:17.690 --> 00:04:19.290
GERARDO ADESSO: Then there is
another interesting property,

00:04:19.290 --> 00:04:21.959
which is slightly more
complicated about this number.

00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:26.630
And it is the fact that it's
defined to be a primary

00:04:26.630 --> 00:04:28.800
pseudoperfect number.

00:04:28.800 --> 00:04:29.860
JAMES GRIME: A what?

00:04:29.860 --> 00:04:32.285
GERARDO ADESSO: A primary
pseudoperfect number.

00:04:32.285 --> 00:04:33.540
JAMES GRIME: Go on, what
does that mean?

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:36.620
GERARDO ADESSO: OK, so first of
all, you have to find out

00:04:36.620 --> 00:04:38.820
what are the prime
factors of 42.

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:46.900
OK, so write down 42 as 2 times
3, which is 6 times 7.

00:04:46.900 --> 00:04:48.920
So these are its
prime factors.

00:04:48.920 --> 00:04:53.240
Primary to the perfect number
is such that the sum of the

00:04:53.240 --> 00:04:56.980
inverse of each prime factor
plus the sum of the inverse of

00:04:56.980 --> 00:04:58.540
the number itself is 1.

00:04:58.540 --> 00:05:06.700
1 over 2 plus 1 over 3 plus 1
over 7, and these are the sum

00:05:06.700 --> 00:05:09.660
of the inverses of each
prime factor.

00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:12.660
Then plus 1 over the
number itself.

00:05:12.660 --> 00:05:15.240
If you work out this
calculation, you can put

00:05:15.240 --> 00:05:18.550
everything under the
common denominator.

00:05:18.550 --> 00:05:20.210
The result is one.

00:05:20.210 --> 00:05:23.120
There are not so many numbers
that have this property.

00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:27.980
The next one after 42
is, I think 1,806.

00:05:27.980 --> 00:05:30.850
And then you immediately go
to very huge numbers.

00:05:30.850 --> 00:05:33.370
So it appears like
any [INAUDIBLE]

00:05:33.370 --> 00:05:34.740
property, but it's not.

00:05:34.740 --> 00:05:36.735
JAMES GRIME: The story
is he sat--

00:05:36.735 --> 00:05:39.540
